  "text": "Basic time-series diagnostics also revealed that the year-to-year variability in one of the AR4 records -the stacked δ 18 O series from Greenland -steadily increased prior to ∼1100, and that this record had a power-spectrum that is both different from all other records and indicative of limited preservation of low-frequency climate variability (Fig. 3) . Variance drifts, often artificial and related to replication changes, . Multi-proxy record from E Asia labeled with an arrow to highlight the varying shape of the spectral density of this lower resolution time series are widespread in proxy-records, and for example, confuse the estimation of extreme year return intervals and the magnitude, in degrees C, of past climatic fluctuations [CITATION_1] . Such time-series qualities (variance drift, \"whiter\" spectrum), increase the probability for a record to be anomalous, and are not supportive for an estimation of long-term climatic change.",
